    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know i should ask my doctor but they're super expensive and i can't get a hold of them until monday. i'm just worried about waking up in a coma or something because i barely ate. if i just skip the basal tonight since i'm already low, isnt that safer than taking it and having a crash? it seems like common sense that less food means less insulin is needed.",
